### === Goal
### ______________________________________________________________

I want following in firefox.

 1. "C-c 1" opens english-korean.
 2. "C-c 3" opens the file "worknote.muse" with emacs.


### === Requrements
### ______________________________________________________________

 1. https://addons.mozilla.org/en-us/firefox/addon/mozlab/


### === Using
### ______________________________________________________________

 1. Install oswk.xpi in firefox. If no oswk.xpi, command "bash oswk.sh"
 will generate oswk.xpi. Or manually install "oswk".

 2. Execute "python moz_server.py". There is no way to execute file in
 firefox. So I wrote a small server to execute "emacsclient" from firefox.
 It uses mozlab to get the information of the firefox window.
